<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0392 </DOCNO><TEXT>Renewable energy and raw material sources attracted more attention whenthe second oil crisis peaked. These include also plants as renewablematerials with a variegated potential for use. Radiation energy fromthe sun is converted to chemical energy by photosynthesis in plants.Depending on the development state of farming and forestry methods andon the plant species cultivated, the ratio of energy yield to expendituremay be over 6:1. With their utilization of the continuously flowing solarenergy, farming and forestry belong to those few branches of nationaleconomy which produce more energy than they consume. Moreover as to productioncost, farming and forestry's dependence from energy prices is negligible,indeed.</TEXT></DOC>